eply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/dooby80/adelphi.jpg length=100 width=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   In combat</span><hr size=1> OK, I told myself I wouldn't do any real dungeons until I got my level 29 spells. So I recently got level 29, and it's been great so far. Got my Swords of Runes, new Burnout, new pets (well, the ones I can buy, since I'm failing earth a bit <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ), things are great. So with my newly acquired skills I went down to the Temple of Cazic Thule.<br>
<br>
Since my main character is a rogue, I am used to combat being very rough and tiring. Running after mobs, grtting backstab positioning, etc. Now with my magician, it seems a LOT easier. This is my first caster actually. And in a good group combat seems VERY easy for us.<br>
<br>
Here is what I have been doing so far. I don't want to feel like a TOTAL loaf and just /pet attack and med all day. I usually summon arrows for the puller, dim pockets if people's fine steel loot gets heavy, stuff like that. When a mob is pulled, I hit everything with malise, send in the pet, and nuke when the mob is about dead. In big battles I damage shield all the pets/fighters (minus monks and shadowknights, in case they have to Feign Death for some reason). I'll nuke more or not at all depending on mana. <br>
<br>
I say a good group, because some groups i've been in, people forget to snare, which results in pet chasing the mob into a bunch of its buddies, which isn't pretty. Others have people switching targets constantly, often leaving my pets to fight a  mob solo. Some people still don't get how impossible it is to pull a pet off of a mob that is aggroing it. <br>
<br>
I bring this topic up because I was asked many interesting questions in a group in the Tae Room tonight. I was asked why I am not doing anything, why I wasn't casting area effect spells, and why I was hardly nuking (when there is a monk, rogue and wizard in the group there isn't much for me to nuke). But I figured I'd ask the people who know, those being you guys. Is what you guys do in everyday combat (or the basics, don't know how higher level spells change this) any different? <p>Adelphi Etrigan
Conjurer and scholar of the Spurned.
Lanys T.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ureaperrp.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ReaperRP</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 114<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 8:01:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: In combat</span><hr size=1> In a group, my general job is to summon the various items needed, get a good pet (usually air in a group for stuns), and damage shield the puller/main tank. I usually stick a malise on at the start of the fight too. Occasionally I throw in a nuke or two, but I try to conserve mana and only start unloading the nukes when :-<br>
