<br>
With enough melee power, lots of nuking usually isn't required. It may sound cheesy, but your pet is pulling a good amount of your weight during these fights, and is virtually resource-free -- no mana required other than the initial summoning, and any damage the pet might take (if any) will be recovered naturally before the rest of the group is ready for the next fight.<br>
<br>
Typically, breaking a room/camp is when the big guns get used. After that, you can start to be more subtle. Here's what I look at in group situations when deciding how much to burn:<br>
<br>
- My mana status<br>
- Healer(s) mana status (usually they're good about letting us know)<br>
- Melee health status<br>
- Main target's health status<br>
- Number of mobs remaining<br>
<br>
The way I look at it, if I'm full mana and the front-line guys are low health, I'm doing something wrong. The opposite also holds true. If I'm low mana and the front-line guys are basically untouched, I'm doing something wrong. This is different when playing my enchanter and we get big pulls, as it's then my job to trade my mana for melee hit points, since I'm never doing damage to the mobs anyway.<br>
<br>
As a rule of thumb, I'll normally lob a nuke in once the mob is half health or below. Depending on the factors above, I might nuke more and earlier, or not at all. You just want to make sure that you're not unprepared for the next fight by being out of mana or having your melee folks more beaten up than they needed to be.<br>
<br>
Sure, there are times when you will want to open up your cannons, especially on named mobs or if the fight isn't going as well as you would have liked. But for the bread-and-butter mobs, try and keep your group resources (mana and health) balanced as best you can.<br>
<br>
I don't have an answer for you about the AE spells. My main character is the enchanter so of course I frown upon their use in a dungeon situation, and my mage's regular group has a really good enchanter so I never get to use them myself. So if you're without an enchanter they may have a good use, though I'd have to defer to someone who's used them in that kind of situation to explain their effectiveness, aggro considerations, etc. <p><body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">

