Artie's post is very good.   In a full group you want to keep up with the pace of the group.  I usually let my mana bounce between 20 and 80 percent but try and keep it about even with the group's pull speed.  In a lot of battles it boils down to malise, dmg shield, and one blast (maybe two on harder creatures).   If you look at the dmg output of the dmg shield, pet, and 1-2 blasts you will definately be pulling your weight.  Overblasting just tends to slow down the group because they have to wait for your mana to go back up.  Having a bubble or two in reserve comes in very handy when a bad pull happens.   <br>
<br>
During the mid levels your priorities should be to malise the MoB and cast dmg shield on the tank who will take the most damage.  Damage shield is the most mana-efficient damage spell we have and it really does rack up good damage.  The trick is to not be the wizard... you aren't the big finisher, but you are the high damage output caster.. your pet, dmg shield, and 1-2 blasts are going to contribute a *lot* to the party.   <p> <br>
<b>Ez</b> <br>
<i>"Good... Bad... I'm the guy with the fire elemental."</i><br><i>"Shop Smart. Shop Ez-Mart!"</i><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uorndorfburninghands.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Orndorf Burninghands</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 6:00:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Strategy</span><hr size=1> In a group as Artie said its all about pace.  Also the area of effect thing lol thats dead on.  If you want to be a dead caster really quick go right ahead.  In a group i malaise, dmg shield the tank and nuke when the tank tells me to add.  Thats whats great about being a mage though.  You are versatile and most people dont realize the true nuking potential we have.  We can light a mob up next to only the wiz  in power but its preferable for us to help maintain the group balance and simply polish the mob off with a final nuke or some such thing.<br>
<br>
Orndorf <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unefariusgnome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nefarius Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 8:07:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Strategy</span><hr size=1> It's good to hear that my tactics seem to be about in line with how other's play magicians. Once the camp is flowing smoothly, the pulls are regular and one at a time, I rarely cast anything except Malise at the beginning of the fight, and Inferno shield on the tank just before he goes to pull.<br>
<br>
If it's just me and my wife, then I'll sometimes heal my pet, but all in all, I don't do much casting while hunting. My wife, on the other hand, is a necro and uses quite a bit of mana casting DoTs, stuns, and so forth. Fortunately, she has her Allure of Death line of spells so that she always regains her mana quickly.<br>
<br>
If I'm full of mana and the pet's healthy, then I'll start tossing the occassional nuke, for lack of anything better to do. But, like others have already said, I generally conserve the big guns for emergencies. (Heh, the other day, camping the WC druids, I would occasionally use Cinder Bolt, which at my level does 322 damage. The wizard in our group was jealous, because none of his nukes did that much damage. At this level, his damage output is higher than mine because of lower casting times, but my nuke was bigger.)<br>
<br>
Oh, and anybody who wants you to use AoE in Cazic Thule is crazy in the head.   <p><p><font face="Arial" COLOR="blue" size="2"><b>Nefarius Frobozz</b><br>Devout Agnostic Gnome Magician of the 35th Trial<i><br>Terris-Thule<br></i></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/unabienincinerador.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nabien Incinerador</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/fire10.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 132<br> <font color=#333333>(11/9/00 8:17:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=94.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/explose3.gif WIDTH=96 HEIGHT=156></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Strategy</span><hr size=1> In a group, usually I just upkeep my pet, refresh group damage sheild, make anything people need and toss in some malosi's.  In the event of something wrong (listed in other posts) I open up the guns.  Generally I don't nuke unless I'm FM though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   (pet carries your weight itself <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/nabieneq/Sig1test.jpg> <BR>
